16_17	0.25	Cox-2 drugs are not more effective, just safer.
16_18	0.09090909090909091	They are easier on the stomach and can be taken in larger doses for a longer time without damage to the stomach or kidneys.
16_19	0.0	They could be on pharmacy shelves by early 1999.
16_20	0.5263157894736842	``It's one of the most exciting developments in the treatment of arthritis in 25 years because we potentially will be able to treat people for their pain and inflammation without them suffering the side effects,'' says Rubin.
16_21	0.2857142857142857	Cox-2 drugs are a type of nonsteroidal anti-inflammatories, such as Naproxen and Ibuprofen.
16_22	0.625	Anti-inflammatories are drugs that reduce both pain and swelling by neutralizing the enzymes that cause them.
16_23	0.0	Researchers have identified two types of this enzyme: cox-1, which releases chemicals that protect the stomach against peptic ulcers, and cox-2, which releases chemicals that cause inflammation.
16_24	0.0	The old class of drugs inhibited both enzymes.
16_25	0.07692307692307693	The new class of drugs selectively works against cox-2 enzymes _ without inhibiting the cox-1 enzymes that protect the stomach.
16_26	0.0	It's a development that could be worth billions.
16_27	0.0	Arthritis sufferers spend millions to pay for unproven alternatives because it gives them a sense of mastery over their pain and because they mistakenly believe that traditional medicine has nothing to offer, says Dr.
16_28	0.0	Doyt Conn, senior vice president for medical affairs for the Arthritis Foundation.
16_29	0.0	``The problem is, the public's misconception that tends to lump all forms of arthritis into one package, and to assume that it's an inevitable part of aging and nothing can be done about it _ all misconceptions,'' Conn says.
16_30	0.1	The term ``arthritis'' includes more than 100 disorders that attack cartilage in the bone joints.
16_31	0.08333333333333333	The disease causes pain, swelling and loss of movement when bone rubs against bone after the cartilage has deteriorated.
16_32	0.0	The best treatment depends on the specific diagnosis.
16_33	0.625	MORE Among the most common types of arthritis: OSTEOARTHRITIS, or degenerative joint disease.
16_34	0.5714285714285714	Affects an estimated 15.8 million Americans, mostly over age 45.
16_35	0.7857142857142857	It involves the breakdown of cartilage and bones through wear-and-tear injuries, and is most often found in the fingers and weight-bearing joints including the knees, feet, hips and back.
16_36	0.0	RHEUMATOID ARTHRITIS.
16_37	0.25	One of the most serious and disabling types, affecting an estimated 2.1 million Americans.
16_38	0.06666666666666667	It involves a genetic abnormality in the body's immune system that causes inflammation in the lining of the joints that can damage cartilage and bone.
16_39	0.0	It often leads to crippling deformities in the hands, wrists, feet, knees, ankles, shoulders, neck, jaw and elbows.
16_40	0.0	JUVENILE ARTHRITIS.
16_41	0.0	A general term for all types of arthritis that occur in children.
16_42	0.0	An estimated 300,000 children in this country have the disease; most have juvenile rheumatoid arthritis.
16_43	0.15384615384615385	FIBROMYALGIA. Affects approximately 3.7 million Americans, causing pain and tenderness at points where muscles attach to bones.
16_44	0.0	People with fibromyalgia frequently experience fatigue, disturbed sleep, stiffness and sometimes psychological distress.
16_45	0.0	GOUT. A painful condition that most often attacks small joints, especially in the big toe.
16_46	0.0	It is caused by a defect in body chemistry and usually can be controlled with medication and changes in diet.
16_47	0.0	BURSITIS AND TENDINITIS.
16_48	0.0	Result from irritation caused by injuring or overusing a joint.
16_49	0.0	Bursitis affects a small sac that helps muscles move easily.
16_50	0.0	Tendinitis affects the tendons that attach muscles to bone.
16_51	0.0	It is critically important to first find out what kind of arthritis you have, according to the experts.
16_52	0.0	``Usually there are lifestyle measures that are very important,'' Conn says.
16_53	0.0	``If you have osteoarthritis of the knee and you are 20 pounds overweight, that weight is a big factor.
16_54	0.0	You need to know what exercising, what conditioning you should be doing''.
16_55	0.0	The earlier that diagnosis is made, the more hope there is for living well into old age with even the most crippling forms.
16_56	0.0	For example, only in the past few years have experts recommended very early, aggressive treatment for rheumatoid arthritis with disease-modifying drugs such as methotrexate (first developed for cancer treatment).
16_57	0.0	The National Institutes of Health reported last month that arthritis is now the leading cause of disability among Americans older than 15, as measured by federal disability payments.
16_58	0.0	The surge of aging baby boomers and the growing number of children who have the disease put arthritis ahead of heart disease, the leading cause of disability payments in a similar study in 1989.
16_59	0.0	More than $65 billion a year in Social Security disability payments goes to the 21 million arthritis sufferers who are unable to work because of their disease, according to the Arthritis Foundation.
16_60	0.0	In comparison, about $50 billion a year in disability payments goes to 17 million heart disease patients.
