21_1	0.4	One new type of painkiller, known as COX-2 inhibitors, just hit pharmacy shelves.
21_2	0.5	The drugs appear to be no more effective at fighting pain than traditional anti-inflammatory medications such as ibuprofen and aspirin, but offer the advantage of fewer side effects.
21_3	0.08333333333333333	That is a major plus for people who must use pain relievers long-term and risk such problems as stomach bleeding and ulcers.
