21_9	0.0	Industry analysts view the drugs as potential blockbusters, likely to command at least 10 percent of the market for common pain relievers.
21_10	0.09090909090909091	COX-2 drugs are designed primarily for those with rheumatoid arthritis, which afflicts about 2.1 million people in the United States, and for painful flareups of osteoarthritis, the ``wear-and-tear'' form of the ailment, which affects an estimated 20.7 million people.
