21_12	0.0	The drugs are generally effective but can be harmful with constant use.
21_13	0.0	A 1997 study of arthritis patients showed at least 107,000 hospitalizations and 16,500 deaths a year from NSAID-related problems.
21_14	0.3	COX-2 drugs block production of an enzyme called cyclooxygenase-2, which produces painful inflammation.
21_15	0.0	Unlike NSAIDs, however, they do not interfere with the closely related COX-1 enzyme, which helps build a protective lining in the stomach and gastrointestinal tract.
21_16	0.0	Searle began selling Celebrex for $2.42 per 200 milligram pill, less than expected but still more than some HMOs might be willing to pay, especially for patients without a demonstrated problem with NSAIDs.
