22_13	0.0	Nothing except heart disease causes more disability, and no disease robs more people of their ability to walk, climb stairs, and even do something as simple as rise from a sitting position.
22_14	0.0	Fortunately, ``there's a lot of progress in osteoarthritis,'' says rheumatologist David T.
